{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01V55GJY6jDxRrfT4VqwRdkV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→MODULE: src/bot\n     2→FILES: 8 (+31 command handlers in commands/handlers/)\n     3→RESPONSIBILITY: Telegram bot — message handling, command routing, file delivery, streaming output\n     4→INTERFACES:\n     5→- createTelegramBot(): Promise<Telegraf> — initialize bot with all command handlers and services\n     6→- bot._f018.subscribeCrossChannel(chatId): void — subscribe realtimeHub for cross-channel push\n     7→KEY_FILES:\n     8→- telegram.js: Main bot setup, text handler, file handling, stream publisher (~1040 lines)\n     9→- commands/index.js: Command registry and routing\n    10→- commands/help.js: Help text generation\n    11→- commands/handlers/output.js: F-020 /output [N] command — view recent AI CLI output history\n    12→DEPENDENCIES:\n    13→- uses: telegraf: Telegram bot framework\n    14→- imports: src/services/ai-cli-service.js: executeAiCli, interruptAiCli\n    15→- imports: src/services/message-router.js: F-018 unified message routing\n    16→- imports: src/services/session-bind.js: F-018 session binding for cross-channel\n    17→- imports: src/services/realtime-hub.js: F-018 event subscription for cross-channel push\n    18→- imports: src/services/session-store.js: session state\n    19→- imports: src/services/chat-service.js: legacy (still imported for /reset command)\n    20→- imports: src/utils/ansi-adapter.js: F-020 processChunk — strips ANSI before Telegram display\n    21→- imports: src/utils/output-segmenter.js: F-020 segmentOutput — logical boundary splitting\n    22→- imports: src/bot/commands/handlers/output.js: F-020 /output command + outputHistoryService singleton\n    23→TRAPS:\n    24→- Telegram bot text handler uses messageRouter.processMessage() (F-018) — no longer calls executeAiCli directly\n    25→- Cross-channel push only subscribes for bindings that exist at bot startup; dynamic bindings via API need manual subscribeCrossChannel() call\n    26→- Heartbeat progress messages disabled after F-018 migration to messageRouter (messageRouter lacks onHeartbeat hook)\n    27→- bot._f018 is an internal namespace — not a stable public API\n    28→- onAssistantChunk wraps chunk with ansiProcessChunk() (F-020) before pushing to streamPublisher — raw ANSI bytes from stdout are never forwarded to Telegram\n    29→- segmentOutput() replaces splitMessage() in render() inside createEditableStreamPublisher — ONLY in streaming path; cross-channel push (subscribeCrossChannel) still uses splitMessage()\n    30→- STREAM_MIN_CHARS (220) and STREAM_FLUSH_INTERVAL_MS (1200) are preserved unchanged — segmentation only changes where cuts happen, not how often\n    31→- outputHistoryService singleton exported from output.js — telegram.js imports it; tests must inject mock via handlerCtx to avoid mutating shared singleton state\n    32→UPDATED: 2026-03-22\n    33→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ec3f85f9-8701-4b0b-90d5-41b254af0c38","uuid":"ef84b8de-683b-4f29-a675-7b709d005011","timestamp":"2026-03-22T17:22:31.654Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizm-docs/src/bot.prizm","content":"MODULE: src/bot\nFILES: 8 (+31 command handlers in commands/handlers/)\nRESPONSIBILITY: Telegram bot — message handling, command routing, file delivery, streaming output\nINTERFACES:\n- createTelegramBot(): Promise<Telegraf> — initialize bot with all command handlers and services\n- bot._f018.subscribeCrossChannel(chatId): void — subscribe realtimeHub for cross-channel push\nKEY_FILES:\n- telegram.js: Main bot setup, text handler, file handling, stream publisher (~1040 lines)\n- commands/index.js: Command registry and routing\n- commands/help.js: Help text generation\n- commands/handlers/output.js: F-020 /output [N] command — view recent AI CLI output history\nDEPENDENCIES:\n- uses: telegraf: Telegram bot framework\n- imports: src/services/ai-cli-service.js: executeAiCli, interruptAiCli\n- imports: src/services/message-router.js: F-018 unified message routing\n- imports: src/services/session-bind.js: F-018 session binding for cross-channel\n- imports: src/services/realtime-hub.js: F-018 event subscription for cross-channel push\n- imports: src/services/session-store.js: session state\n- imports: src/services/chat-service.js: legacy (still imported for /reset command)\n- imports: src/utils/ansi-adapter.js: F-020 processChunk — strips ANSI before Telegram display\n- imports: src/utils/output-segmenter.js: F-020 segmentOutput — logical boundary splitting\n- imports: src/bot/commands/handlers/output.js: F-020 /output command + outputHistoryService singleton\nTRAPS:\n- Telegram bot text handler uses messageRouter.processMessage() (F-018) — no longer calls executeAiCli directly\n- Cross-channel push only subscribes for bindings that exist at bot startup; dynamic bindings via API need manual subscribeCrossChannel() call\n- Heartbeat progress messages disabled after F-018 migration to messageRouter (messageRouter lacks onHeartbeat hook)\n- bot._f018 is an internal namespace — not a stable public API\n- onAssistantChunk wraps chunk with ansiProcessChunk() (F-020) before pushing to streamPublisher — raw ANSI bytes from stdout are never forwarded to Telegram\n- segmentOutput() replaces splitMessage() in render() inside createEditableStreamPublisher — ONLY in streaming path; cross-channel push (subscribeCrossChannel) still uses splitMessage()\n- STREAM_MIN_CHARS (220) and STREAM_FLUSH_INTERVAL_MS (1200) are preserved unchanged — segmentation only changes where cuts happen, not how often\n- outputHistoryService singleton exported from output.js — telegram.js imports it; tests must inject mock via handlerCtx to avoid mutating shared singleton state\nUPDATED: 2026-03-22\n","numLines":33,"startLine":1,"totalLines":33}}}
